Chilean Stocks: E-CL SA, Lan Airlines SA and Salfacorp SA Rise

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-16T21:11:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/chilean-stocks-lan-airlines-quinenco-soquimich-shares-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:33 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.1 percent to 4,855.  E-CL SA (ECL CC) gained 1.9 percent to a record 1,370.6
pesos. The northern Chilean power generator received 40.9
billion pesos ($86.8 million) in tax rebates from the state that
will be used to pay debts, according to a filing posted on the
website of  Chile ’s securities regulator.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)  ,  Latin America ’s largest airline
by market value, rose 0.1 percent to 13,461 pesos. A decline in
oil prices signaled lower costs for transport companies.  Salfacorp SA (SALFACOR)  , Chile’s largest engineering and
construction company, gained 0.6 percent to 1,782.2 pesos.
Consalfa SAS, a Colombian company in which Salfacorp and
Conconcreto SA each own 50 percent, agreed to pay $32 million
for 80 percent of Panamanian builder Intercoastal Marine Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
